{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"],"tokens":[{"text":"@interface","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MLNMapSnapshotter","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSObject","text":"NSObject","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can change the snapshotter’s options at any time and reuse the snapshotter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for multiple distinct snapshots; however, the snapshotter can only generate one"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"snapshot at a time. If you need to generate multiple snapshots concurrently,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"create multiple snapshotter objects."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For an interactive map, use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","isActive":true},{"text":" class. Both ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapSnapshotter","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","isActive":true},{"text":" are compatible with offline packs managed by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOfflineStorage","isActive":true},{"text":" class.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"From a snapshot, you can obtain an image and convert geographic coordinates to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the image’s coordinate space in order to superimpose markers and overlays. If",